-- Tepco Idles Unit Cutting Japan Nuclear Capacity to 8.1%
-- B y   T s u y o s h i   I n a j i m a
-- 2012-01-25T06:42:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-25/tepco-idles-unit-cutting-japan-nuclear-capacity-to-8-1-table-.html
Japan  has four nuclear reactors
operating today with capacity of 3,958 megawatts, or 8.1 percent
of the total, after a unit was idled yesterday, according to
data compiled by Bloomberg News.  Tokyo Electric Power Co. shut the 1,100-megawatt No. 5
reactor at its Kashiwazaki Kariwa plant in northern Japan
yesterday for regular maintenance, spokesman Masato Yamaguchi
said by phone today. The utility known as Tepco plans to halt
the last operating reactor at the worldâ€™s biggest nuclear
station by the end of March, he said.  The following table shows the status of the 54 reactors
with capacity of 48,960 megawatts operated by Japanese power
companies. Capacity figures are in megawatts.  
